class Solution {
public:
    int brokenCalc(int startValue, int target) {
        int res = 0;
        while (target > startValue) {
            if (target % 2 == 1) target++;
            target /= 2;
            res++;
        }
        return res + (startValue - target);
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(target))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The algorithm uses a greedy approach to minimize the number of operations. It keeps dividing the target by 2 as long as it's odd, and increments the result counter. Finally, it adds the remaining difference between startValue and target to the result.

